description:
File: lichen/subsys/lichen/oscore/coap_oscore.c
Lines: 108-116

The coap_oscore_unprotect_request function dereferences request_piv_len before validating opt.has_piv:

```c
/* Save request PIV for response */
if (opt.has_piv && opt.piv_len > 0) {
    if (*request_piv_len < opt.piv_len) {  // Dereference of request_piv_len
        return OSCORE_ERR_BUFFER_TOO_SMALL;
    }
    memcpy(request_piv, opt.piv, opt.piv_len);
    *request_piv_len = opt.piv_len;
} else {
    *request_piv_len = 0;  // Also dereference
}
```

If request_piv_len is NULL (violating _Nonnull contract), this crashes. While the function signature marks it as _Nonnull, defensive programming should check:

```c
if (request_piv == NULL || request_piv_len == NULL) {
    return OSCORE_ERR_INVALID_PARAM;
}
```

The _Nonnull annotation is a hint for static analyzers but doesn't prevent runtime NULL values.

Severity: Medium - relies on caller following contract, but no runtime enforcement.
